summary: “Coulson. The new guy... I guess he had a feeling...”  I love this scene because, you know what? That is exactly the kind of man...
caption:
“Coulson. The new guy… I guess he had a feeling…”

I love this scene because, you know what? That is exactly the kind of man Phil Coulson was. Before Loki, before Tahiti, before Daisy and the Inhumans and Hive and all the rest of it, Phil Coulson was just a really good guy. His loyalty to his friends, his trust in his instincts, his compassion and willingness to risk everything in order to do the right thing. He’s an average guy, not a genius or a super soldier or a god, but he’s the best of us.

Having said that, if the super soldier serum had been developed in the nineties, Phil Coulson would have made a pretty fantastic Captain America. It’s why he won Stark’s trust, it’s why his death motivated the team to come together, it’s why he kept S.H.I.E.L.D. going after the fall and it’s why Fury didn’t hesitate to call him exactly what he always was. An Avenger.

title: Video Games With Brie
body:
Prompt: “ Playing video games with Brie hcs??? “            

its kinda short but i hope you still like it. sorry for the wait btw @dinkleberg-senpai

again just like with the dates variety is key but also I feel  like she’s a fan of the old skul stuff so

- pokemon on the gameboy for sure -> means you two sitting on the couch on rainy days wrapped in blankets as you two play side by side with hot cocoa next to you

- mario kart (every version you can think of) battles for the last pizza piece or to settle petty arguments lol

- puzzle and point and click stuff to relax when you ran out of movies and tv shows to watch

- I think she kinda is a little competitive and a bit of an asshole when she wins so she will kinda rub it in your face or be at least cocky about it somehow haha but when its a long game night and you’ve been losing a lot she will slip up ‘accidentally’ and let you win, giving you congratulation kisses

- sometimes just watching her play whatever and sitting in between her legs as she plays with her arms around you as you read a book or the other way around when you wanna play

- testing new stuff whenever you can, new vr technologies or whatever

- visiting arcades for sure

- karaoke and dance battle games are high on her list of course

- just having so much fun with her playing around and rewinding from the stressful stuff going on around you
